bucket/object location, workflow lineage, and
parent/master IDs in ACTIVE, CREATING, or
UPDATING
conflicts: none
open gaps: none
Reviewed lifecycle mapping treats CREATING as
provisioning, UPDATING as updating, ACTIVE as
success, FAILED as terminal without requeue, and
DELETING as terminating until follow-up
observation reaches DELETED or OCI NotFound.
Create, get, and update return the MediaAsset
body directly, while DeleteMediaAsset returns
only opc-request-id. The reviewed runtime
therefore stays lifecycle-based and does not
publish work-request polling behavior.
The published delete contract is intentionally
narrow: DeleteMediaAsset is called without
deleteMode or isLockOverride, so hierarchical
delete modes DELETE_CHILDREN and
DELETE_DERIVATIONS remain out of scope for the
controller-backed surface.
Matching create-time locks are normalized by
ignoring OCI-populated timeCreated metadata so
steady-state reconcile does not fail after a
successful create that requested locks.
end note
note right of delete_pending
delete policy: required
delete observe: GetMediaAsset or ListMediaAssets
delete targets: DELETED
end note
